---
description: "Architecture and layering constraints for service modules"
alwaysApply: false
globs:
  - "src/**/*.h"
  - "src/**/*.hpp"
  - "src/**/*.cc"
  - "src/**/*.cpp"
  - "include/**/*.h"
  - "include/**/*.hpp"
---

- Keep transport, protocol, business logic, storage, and utility concerns separated where the existing codebase allows.
- Do not mix protocol parsing with business decision logic unless nearby code already follows that pattern.
- Prefer explicit ownership and dependency injection over hidden global mutable state.
- Avoid adding new shared utility modules unless at least two real call sites justify them.
- When extending a flow, prefer following the existing request lifecycle instead of inserting side paths.
- If adding a new component, explain where it belongs in the current layering.
